General conditions: 
1. The Freight Forwarder obligates: 
1.1. to provide transport services according to this booking, deliver cargo to destination point stated and hand over it to a consignee with all documents, related to it in compliance to all legal requirements. 
1.2. confirm or return a booking to the Customer in 8 hours after a booking received, stating objective reason for this action, without any obligations to compensate possible or already occurred losses of the Customer; 
1.3. suspend proceeding with cargo transportation requested by this booking of the Customer, if there is some essential information missing until this information in not received, sending prior notification about it to the Customer; 
1.4. receive support from third party in providing transportation services to the Customer, following conditions of this booking. 
2. The Customer obligated to:
2.1. transmit a booking to the Freight Forwarder by any mean of communication channel (fax, internet, e-mail, etc.) 48 hours before the Freight Forwarder is expected to take an action;
2.2. submit to the Freight Forwarder all information necessary to carry specific cargo and all documents necessary for fulfillment of this booking;
2.3. ensure appropriateness of a shipment’s packaging for transportation;
2.4. compensate to the Freight Forwarder losses occurred due to inaccuracy or incompleteness of indicated in a booking data.
2.5. inform the Freight Forwarder about any changes in conditions, not later 24 hours before cargo transportation will take place;
2.6. ensure payment of the invoice for the services provided under conditions of this booking.
2.7. make any changes in this booking sent to the Freight Forwarder or cancel it in not less then 48 hours before cargo transportation, without any obligations to compensate possible or already occurred losses of the Freight Forwarder.
3. Settlement of payment for the services:
3.1. the Customer obligates compensate to the Freight Forwarder the expenditures of fulfillment of the booking and agreed payment of a invoice issued according to the terms stated in this booking;
3.2. in the case of delayed against the invoice submitted by the Freight Forwarder, the Customer shall pay a fine of 0,2% for every delayed day of the due amount.
4. Liabilities of the parties:
4.1. all services provided to the Customer according to this booking conditions and liability of the Freight Forwarder is regulated by legal acts of the Republic of Lithuania, international conventions and agreements:
• Warsaw convention from year 1929 and its adjustments from year 1955 on air freight under airway bill (AWB);
• Geneva convention from year 1956 m. on road freight under international transportation document (CMR);
• Visby rules from year 1968 on sear freight under Bill of Lading (B/L);
• Bern convention from year 1964 on railway freight under international transportation document (SMGS).
4.2. the Freight Forwarder is not responsible for legal actions of customs or other state institutions, related to examination of a cargo, its temporary suspendment, confiscation and etc. while transportation services are provided according to this booking. Herewith the Customer obligated to compensate loses of the Freight Forwarder related to such actions;
5. Place of arbitration:
All disputes arising from the fulfillment of the booking shall be settled in negotiations and in case of dispute according to the Court practice of the Republic of Lithuania in Kaunas town.
